nominalLexeme: 1. An institution or part of an institution that keeps books and newspapers for people to read. A member is usually allowed to borrow books for certain periods of time. English = library.
2. A person who is in charge of a library or who has been trained to do responsible work in a library. English = librarian.
oldEntry: Popular explanation: derived from the name sign for a past librarian at the Victorian School for the Deaf.
